Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant Robert W. Becker in court with attorney Steven Hughes.  

Defendant enters a plea of Guilty to count 1.
Court finds the defendant Guilty of count 1.
Court 2 is dismissed as a read in.

FELONY WARNINGS PROVIDED:  REGARDING VOTING AND FIREARMS RESTRICTIONS.

Court orders the followng:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.
4 Days Credit - IF REVOKED.

Term of Probation:  2 Years.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
COMPLIANCE WITH THE OWI TREATMENT COURT.
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
Installation of the Ignition Interlock Device;
Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel;
Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license;
DNA sample to be provided;

D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

CONDITION TIME:
300 Days Jail
First 60 Days in the Waukesha County Jail w/Huber (all standard release conditions) - FORTHWITH.
Balance of 240 days jail to be served - STRAIGHT-TIME.

FINE: $ 1,569
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department
APPLY BAIL - BALANCE to be paid as a Condition of the Sentence.

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.
